			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3672352">
									

<p>Maybe I have a different understanding of 'donation link' to other people, but this is ambiguously worded and doesn't answer my question (although I'll assume that since you linked that section of the policy, the answer is 'no').</p>
<p>I wouldn't consider, say, www.redcross.org to be a 'donation link', and it doesn't address the question of whether I can say 'please donate to the Red Cross if you liked this article'. A rule against advertising 'proceeds going to X' implies to me that I may not collect money and advertise it as being on a third party's behalf, not that I can't suggest people take their money elsewhere without me being involved.</p>

